HEADWORD: Ludlamite
<hw>Lud"lam*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<person>Mr. <etsep>Ludlam</etsep></person>, of London.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in small, green, transparent,
monoclinic crystals. It is a hydrous phosphate of iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ludlow group</ent>⟦br⟧
